sentences: Pascal Rogé (born 6 April 1951) is a French pianist.
Rogé first appearance in public was in 1960 with a performance of Claude Debussy's Préludes.
In 2011 he and his wife Ami premiered the Concerto for Two Pianos by the Australian composer Matthew Hindson, which was commissioned to celebrate their recent wedding.
He won the piano prize at the Paris Conservatory and worked for several years with Julius Katchen.
